# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Welcome to the Crime Platform onboarding process. This guide will walk you through obtaining access to non-live and/or live tenants step by step.

## Overview

The onboarding journey consists of the following steps:

1. [Generate Key Pairs](01-generate-keys.html) - Create your GPG and SSH keys
2. [Request Access](02-request-access.html) - Submit a PR with your public keys
3. [Get Approved](03-get-approved.html) - Wait for Platform Operations team review
4. [Decrypt Credentials](04-decrypt-credentials.html) - Unlock your new Azure password
5. [Azure Portal](05-azure-portal.html) - Log in and configure MFA
6. [Obtain Secrets](06-obtain-vpn-gauth-secrets.html) - Retrieve and decrypt your VPN and Authenticator secrets
7. [Configure Authenticator](07-configure-google-auth.html) - Add your Authenticator App
8. [Configure VPN](08-vpn-config.html) - Set up your VPN connection
9. [Configure DNS](09-dns-config.html) - Set up your DNS configuration
10. [Configure SSH](10-ssh-config.html) - Add SSH for platform access

